Remnant of the core of a massive star.

## Discovery

In 1967 [pulsars](pulsar) were discovered -- first thought to be radio signals from alien civilisation.

## Formation

In [type-II supernova](supernova) explosion.

## Properties

Rapid rotation, due to conservation of angular momentum:

$P_{ns}=P_{c}\left(\frac{R_{ns}}{R_{c}}\right)^2\sim 0.005s$

Similarly, intense magnetic field:

$B_{ns}\sim B_c\left(\frac{R_{ns}}{R_c}\right)^2\sim 10^{12}B_{sun}$

High temperature:

$T\sim 10^6K\lambda_{max}=2.9nm$

Luminosity about a quarter of that of the Sun, in x-rays.

## [Chandrasekhar Limit](Chandrasekhar limit)

2.2-2.9 solar masses.

